{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","externalID":"s:12UltraliteSDK12ScrollLayoutC12AutoScrollerC8durationSivp","roleHeading":"Instance Property","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"duration","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int"}],"title":"duration","modules":[{"name":"UltraliteSDK"}],"symbolKind":"property"},"kind":"symbol","hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller"]]},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/duration"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["iOS"],"tokens":[{"text":"var","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"duration"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","text":"Int"},{"text":" { ","kind":"text"},{"text":"get","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"keyword","text":"set"},{"kind":"text","text":" }"}]}]}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/duration","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"abstract":[{"text":"The duration in milliseconds over which we animate text moving between positions. Value 0 indicates instantaneous movement rather than animation.","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller":{"title":"ScrollLayout.AutoScroller","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"AutoScroller","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller","role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"AutoScroller is a utility class to send a large known block of predfined text to the glasses to be smoothly scrolled.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is simlar to what is seen on a teleprompter or in movie credits.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"This class was written using the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ScrollLayout"},{"type":"text","text":" commands and is nothing more than a convience class."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Everything used this class can be written from the public SDK.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"It scrolls the text much like a teleprompter would with basic commands to pause and resume the scrolling.","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"The duration (speed) of the scrolling can be modified while scrolling by seting the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"duration"},{"type":"text","text":" property."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It can support any language that the font supports."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"If the content is not known up front, or subject to change, this is the utility class will not work (use ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"LiveText"},{"text":" instance instead).","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","navigatorTitle":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"AutoScroller"}]},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout/AutoScroller/duration":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"var"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"duration","kind":"identifier"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si","kind":"typeIdentifier"}],"role":"symbol","kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"The duration in milliseconds over which we animate text moving between positions. Value 0 indicates instantaneous movement rather than animation.","type":"text"}],"type":"topic","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout\/autoscroller\/duration","title":"duration","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout\/AutoScroller\/duration"},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK/ScrollLayout":{"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"When Ultralite.requestControl with a .scroll layout type .. this is the class you interate with to draw scrolling text to the screen."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"Once the layout is .scrolled you must send one configure message to tell the layout how to setup.  It will setup the slice height and how many slices are visible.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"There are two supported modes: autoScroll on\/off","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is true, the slices are automatically scrolled.  Subscribe to the delgate and listen for the scrolled callback, when you get it send another slice of text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"When autoScroll is false, you can drive the slices and how they look on the screen.  You can send all the slices at once or send one at a time and animate it onto the screen at the current time."}],"url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk\/scrolllayout","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK\/ScrollLayout","type":"topic","role":"symbol","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}],"kind":"symbol","title":"ScrollLayout","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"ScrollLayout","kind":"identifier"}]},"doc://UltraliteSDK/documentation/UltraliteSDK":{"title":"UltraliteSDK","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/UltraliteSDK\/documentation\/UltraliteSDK","url":"\/documentation\/ultralitesdk","role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Use this SDK to easily send text and images to your Vuxix smart glasses."}],"type":"topic"}}}